  "texts": [
    "IntroductionRecently, the cases of kidney tumors have increased worldwide [1,2].",
    "As one of the malignant tumors affecting the human urinary reproductive system, radical nephrectomy is the most commonly used method in clinical treatment.However, this procedure can result in post-operative issues, causing daily life inconveniences.",
    "Hence, kidney-preserving surgeries are commonly used in tumor treatments [3,4], necessitating the accurate segmentation of the kidney and kidney tumor before surgery [5,6].",
    "However, challenges such as low contrast in the tissue details and the irregular shape of the kidney and tumor in abdominal scanning images can make precise segmentation difficult [7][8][9][10].",
    "Artificial intelligence (AI) has shown potential in assisting clinical care as an effective way to detect and diagnose abnormal areas [11][12][13]."
  ],
